The 1% is applied **between** comparisons. 

```python
def iswin( loss_i, loss_j, time_i, time_j ):
    """
    Determines the winner between two models based on the epsilon adjusted loss.

    Parameters:
        loss_i (float): Loss of uid i on batch
        loss_j (float): Loss of uid j on batch.
        time_i (float): Timestamp of uid i.
        time_j (float): Timestamp of uid j.
    Returns:
        bool: True if loss i is better, False otherwise.
    """
    # Adjust loss based on timestamp and pretrain epsilon
    loss_i = (1 - pretrain.timestamp_epsilon) * loss_i if time_i < time_j else loss_i
    loss_j = (1 - pretrain.timestamp_epsilon) * loss_j if time_j < time_i else loss_j
    return loss_i < loss_j

```

Hey folks. Since this is a breaking update, I want to clarify a few details

First please note this is a NEW github repo, so you'll need to clone it into a new directory: git clone https://github.com/RaoFoundation/pretraining.git

1. Will my old model still be evaluated?

No. You need to first create a **public** hugging face repo and setup your .env with an access token. Then you can use the following to upload your old model.safe file to hugging face
```
python neurons/miner.py --wallet.name CK --wallet.hotkey HK --hf_repo_id my_user/my_repo --load_model path/model.safe --num_epochs 1  --avg_loss_upload_threshold 20
```

2. How do I update my validator?
We recommend the auto-update script: https://github.com/RaoFoundation/pretraining/blob/main/docs/validator.md#with-auto-updates. Since this script uses a git pull --rebase to perform the updates, the auto-update will fail if you have local changes.

3. I want to train a new model architecture. What's supported?
Any subclass of AutomodelForCausalLM (https://github.com/RaoFoundation/pretraining/blob/main/docs/validator.md#with-auto-updates). However, please note that the upload repo size MUST BE < 1 GB and the number of model params must be less than 122,268,040, otherwise the validators weill not eval your model and you will score 0

4. How often can I publish a new model?
At most, once per 20 minutes. However, miner.py and upload_model.py will both retry until the model is successfully published
